# License Overview

This repository contains both hardware design and software code. These distinct components are governed by different open source licenses, as detailed below.

## Hardware Design

The **hardware design** components (including but not limited to schematic diagrams, PCB layouts, Bill of Materials (BOM), and computer-aided design (CAD) files) are licensed under the **Solderpad Hardware License version 2.1**.

> This is a permissive license that allows others to freely use, modify, and distribute your hardware design, even in proprietary products, provided that they give appropriate credit and do not imply endorsement by the original author. It includes a patent license and retaliation clause.

- **Full License Text**: [Solderpad_Hardware_License_v2.1.txt](Solderpad_Hardware_License_v2.1.txt)
- **SPDX Short Identifier**: `Solderpad-2.1` or `Apache-2.0 WITH SHL-2.1`
- **Official Link**: <https://solderpad.org/licenses/SHL-2.1/>

## Software Code

The **software** components (including but not limited to firmware, drivers, application code, and scripts) are licensed under the **Apache License, Version 2.0**.

> This is a permissive license that not only grants copyright and patent licenses, but also includes provisions to prevent patent litigation abuse. It requires preservation of copyright and license notices, and provides explicit patent rights from contributors.

- **Full License Text**: [Apache_License_v2.0.txt](Apache_License_v2.0.txt)
- **SPDX Short Identifier**: `Apache-2.0`
- **Official Link**: <https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0>

## Documentation

The **documentation** (including this file, project wikis, and non-code explanatory texts) is licensed under the **Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License**.

- **Full License Text**: <https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode>
- **SPDX Short Identifier**: `CC-BY-4.0`
- **Human-Readable Summary**: <https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/>

